thread.title_full: MSU stays at No. 7 in AP Top 25; UM slides to No. 15

author: detroitnews.com
title: MSU stays at No. 7 in AP Top 25; UM slides to No. 15
text:
Michigan State quarterback Connor Cook celebrates with the fans as he walks up the tunnel after the game. (Photo: David Guralnick, Detroit News) 
Michigan State’s furious finish wasn’t enough to budge in the national polls.
Michigan State (7-0) remained No. 4 in the coaches poll, and No. 7 in the Top 25 for the second straight week after Saturday’s 27-23 victory over Michigan. The Wolverines (5-2), meanwhile, dropped three spots in each — to No. 15, tied with Texas A&M, in the AP, and No. 17 in the coaches poll.
Ohio State remained No. 1 in both polls. For the second straight week, six teams received first-place votes in the media poll, led by the Buckeyes with 28. No. 2 Baylor has 12, No. 3 Utah received 16, No. 4 TCU got three and No. 5 LSU and No. 6 Clemson each have one.
Utah and LSU each edged ahead one spot after home victories on Saturday.
Pittsburgh (5-1), coached by former Michigan State defensive coordinator Pat Narduzzi, entered the AP poll at No. 25.
